gs I was always aware of is where the guards were and what they would kill if it got too close to them...  most newbies know these things because it is a &quot;safety zone&quot; if you got in over your head with a MoB and were too far from a zone...  <br>
<br>
I died many times because when I got the place where the guard was supposed to be, there was some &quot;high level&quot; killing the guard and I was almost dead so had no chance of making it to the zone...<br>
<br>
Now, at lvl 40, I thought I would not have to deal with the problem any longer.  I guess I was wrong.  I was recently fighting near the RyGorr fort in EW and soloing cents while looking for a group...  occassionally, I would overpull or get an elite or something and I would run to the Dain outpost nearby and get them to take care of the problem for me...   was fine until some &quot;high levels&quot; decided they were gonna use this outpost for faction and killed all the Dain (not during a quest, people usually let the zone know when that is happening)...  I didn't get the names cause I died and they were gone by the time I got back to my corpse...<br>
<br>
I guess my problem is; why kill the &quot;guards&quot; that people use for protection when there are other places where you can get exp or faction?  Do you just not care about anyone else?  Are you too lazy to go find another outpost? Do you need the faction so badly and so quickly that you just have to kill &quot;all&quot; the &quot;guards&quot;? If you kill the &quot;guards,&quot; couldn't you at least kill the mobs that people bring there lookin for protection?</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm12.processVote?topicID=181.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I avoid guards at all cost...</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I only kill em when they attack me...</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I kill em, but I kill mobs for the newbs when I do...</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="4"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I'm an asshole, I kill whatever I want, to hell with everyone else...</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="5"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>You shouldn't run to the guards, just die...</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"></form><a HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm12.showMessage?topicID=181.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p><a href="http://ebonmoon.com/index2.htm" target="_blank"><img src="http://ebonmoon.com/images/kel_bar.jpg" height=85 width=468 alt="Kelwin Jumala, GL - Shadows of the Ebon Moon on Vazaelle" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.show